goals.rationale: This visualization helps to identify the age group of the victims and if there were any specific age groups that were targeted during the LA riots.

goals.rationale: This visualization helps to identify the race of the victims and if there were any specific races that were targeted during the LA riots.

goals.question: What is the relationship between the number of incidents reported and the number of arrests made?
goals.visualization: Scatter plot of the number of incidents reported and the number of arrests made
goals.rationale: This visualization helps to identify if there is any correlation between the number of incidents reported and the number of arrests made during the LA riots.

goals.question: What is the distribution of the type of incidents reported?

goals.rationale: This visualization helps to identify the type of incidents that were reported during the LA riots and if there were any specific types of incidents that were more common than others.

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%m/%d/%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data.sort_values(by='date')
    plt.plot(data['date'], data['incidents'], color='blue')
    plt.title('What is the trend of the number of incidents reported during the LA riots?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('Number of Incidents')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['age'] = pd.to_numeric(data['age'], errors='coerce')
    data = data.dropna(subset=['age'])
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.hist(data['age'], bins=20, color='blue', alpha=0.5)
    ax.set_xlabel('Age')
    ax.set_ylabel('Frequency')
    ax.axvline(data['age'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median Age: {:.2f}'.format(data['age'].median()))
    ax.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of the age of the victims?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Race'].value_counts().plot(kind='bar', color=['red', 'blue', 'green', 'orange', 'purple'])
    plt.title('What is the distribution of the race of the victims?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):

    plt.scatter(data['incidents'], data['arrests'], color='blue')
    plt.xlabel('Number of Incidents Reported')
    plt.ylabel('Number of Arrests Made')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between the number of incidents reported and the number of arrests made?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
